# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // 2π
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // √0.5

// Simulation parameters
var params = {
  yield: 4000,            // Repulsion strength between nodes
  leverage: 0.004,        // Spring stiffness default
  volatility: 0.92,       // Velocity damping factor
  liquidity: 0.0003,      // Centering force strength
  portfolio: 40,          // Max number of particles
  correlation: 0.04,      // Particle friction/drag
  delta: 0.06             // Camera smoothing factor
};

// Nodes (vertices in a force-directed graph)
var nodes = [
  { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Edges (springs connecting nodes)
var edges = [
  { a: "hub",   b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "hub",   b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera system
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle system
var particles = [];
var tick = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// Apply forces to all nodes
function applyForces() {
  // 1. Repulsion between every pair of nodes (like charged particles)
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      var force = params.yield / (dist * dist);
      var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2. Spring attraction along edges
  for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
    var nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
    var nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
    if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
    var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
    var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
    var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    var displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
    var force = (edges[i].k || params.leverage) * displacement;
    nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3. Apply velocity, damping, and centering gravity
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * params.liquidity; // center gravity X
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * params.liquidity;  // center gravity Y
    nodes[i].vx *= params.volatility; // damping
    nodes[i].vy *= params.volatility;
    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx; // integrate position
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}

// Spawn a new particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= params.portfolio) return;
  var node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;
  particles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
  });
}

// Update all particles
function updateParticles() {
  for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    var p = particles[i];
    p.vx *= 1 - params.correlation * 0.125;  // drag
    p.vy *= 1 - params.correlation * 0.125;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1); // remove dead particles
  }
}

// Smooth camera movement toward target
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * params.delta;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * params.delta;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * params.delta;
}

// Main simulation loop
function update() {
  applyForces();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();
  tick++;
  if (tick % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
}

setInterval(update, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** with a particle system, disguised with financial terminology. Here's the breakdown:

### 🔵 Force-Directed Graph Layout
- **6 nodes** ("Hub", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") are connected by **8 edges/springs**
- Nodes **repel** each other (Coulomb-like force inversely proportional to distance²)
- Connected nodes are pulled together by **spring forces** (Hooke's law) with configurable rest lengths and stiffnesses
- A weak **centering gravity** pulls everything toward (400, 300)
- **Velocity damping** (0.92) prevents runaway oscillation

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3 ticks, a particle spawns from a random node
- Particles drift outward in random directions with slight drag
- They have a limited lifespan (800–2000 ticks) and are removed when expired
- Capped at 40 particles max

### 🎥 Smooth Camera
- Camera position lerps toward a target at 6% per frame

### 🎭 The Obfuscation
The financial-sounding parameter names (`yield`, `leverage`, `volatility`, `liquidity`, `portfolio`, `correlation`, `delta`) are purely cosmetic misdirection — this is just a **physics-based node graph animation** running at ~60 FPS, likely intended as a visual/decorative background effect.
